# Mermaid Diagram Standards

Follow these rules when writing or modifying Mermaid diagrams:

* **Dark-Mode CSS Overrides**: Always begin Mermaid code blocks with this contrast-safe initialization header:
  ```mermaid
  %%{init: {
    'theme': 'dark',
    'themeVariables': {
      'background': '#1e1e1e',
      'primaryTextColor': '#ffffff',
      'lineColor': '#a0a0a0',
      'actorBkg': '#2c3e50',
      'actorBorder': '#34495e',
      'actorTextColor': '#ffffff',
      'noteBkgColor': '#2c3e50',
      'noteTextColor': '#ffffff',
      'noteBorderColor': '#34495e'
    },
    'themeCSS': 'svg { background-color: #1e1e1e !important; padding: 1rem !important; border-radius: 8px !important; } .edgeLabel rect { fill: #1e1e1e !important; } text, tspan { fill: #ffffff !important; } .messageText, .messageText tspan, .signalText, .signalText tspan { fill: #ffffff !important; stroke: #1e1e1e !important; stroke-width: 3px !important; paint-order: stroke fill !important; stroke-linejoin: round !important; }'
  }}%%
  ```
* **Text Wrapping**: Wrap node labels using `<br/>` every 2-3 words. Keep individual label lines under 25 characters to prevent diagram overflows.
* **Semantic Colors**: Apply standard style classes to nodes:
  * Failure / Trap / Error (Red): `style nodeID fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff`
  * Success / Solution / Correct Path (Green): `style nodeID fill:#27ae60,color:#fff`
  * Standard Concept / Process (Blue): `style nodeID fill:#2980b9,color:#fff`
